  "summary": "postinstall hook exfiltrates host data to oastify.com via curl",
  "details": "On installation, the package's postinstall lifecycle script executes curl commands that perform HTTP POST requests to a *.oastify.com endpoint (Burp Collaborator / out-of-band interaction infrastructure commonly used to confirm RCE and harvest reconnaissance data). The hook fires automatically during `npm install` without user interaction and sends host information to an attacker-controlled domain. This pattern matches the canonical install-time exfiltration / dependency-confusion proof-of-concept fingerprint and is unsafe to install in any environment.",
